direction-type.words: I think, when I read that sweet story
When Jesus was here among men,
How He called little children as lambs
I should like to have been with them then.
I wish that His hands had been placed
That His arms had been thrown around
And that I might have seen His kind look
"Let the little ones come unto Me."
all who are washed and forgiven;
"of such is the kingdom of heaven."
